headline: California Just Got More Oil-Friendly. One Stock Jumped 21%.
summary: The state legislature passed a bill over the weekend that eases environmental rules for drilling in one section of the state.

headline: Could Phillips 66’s (PSX) New Chief Economist Hint at Shifts in Its Strategic Outlook?
summary: Phillips 66 recently appointed Sean Maher as its new chief economist, effective October 1, succeeding Jeff Dietert who retired after eight years at the company. This leadership change brings in Maher's nearly 30 years of energy finance and investment experience, signaling continuity and potential fresh insights for Phillips 66's global outlook and strategy. We'll explore how the addition of Maher as chief economist could impact Phillips 66’s trajectory and investment narrative moving...
